  <description type="morphology">Plants green, yellow-green, or yellow-brown. Stems with paraphyllia absent; axillary hair distal cells 1–3, linear or shortly so. Stem leaves sometimes more erect when dry, ± recurved, sometimes slightly homomallous, densely or sparsely inserted, 0.2–0.5 mm wide; base erect to almost spreading; acumen 43–62% leaf length; basal alar cells long- to short-rectangular, distal alar cells quadrate to rectangular, alar region large, reaching from margin 40–50% distance to costa at insertion. Seta 1.2–2.2 cm.</description>
